headline: Investor says some Magnificent Seven stocks ‘overly punished’
summary: STORY: Lynch points to companies like Alphabet, Meta and Nvidia as attractive, because they "are still central, they are still guiding for really higher earnings growth." But he’s more cautious on others."We want to see free cash flow yields that are still at least a few percentage points and you know, a name like Oracle, which is growing really fast, that has a negative free cash flow right now is not something we're interested in. Something like Microsoft, that still has a few points, that's okay."

DTE, which provides electricity and natural gas to millions of customers across Michigan, will provide 1.4 gigawatts of power for  Oracle’s  facility after getting approval from the Michigan Public Service Commission.  The deal is DTE’s first with a hyperscale data center, the company said.

headline: Stock Pickers See Their Moment to Shine in Market’s AI Freak-Out
summary: Yes, artificial intelligence is likely to disrupt companies and put some of them out of business.  When a new AI tool threatens to upset an industry, investors are simply selling the whole group.  “We’re having a shakeout, but it’s a good buying opportunity,” said Gina Bolvin Bernarduci, president at Bolvin Wealth Management Group, who says she’s snapping up tech shares after valuations for the group have retreated.
